## Sorting

```typescript
const results = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.orderAsc('title'),       // A ŌåÆ Z, 0 ŌåÆ 9
        Query.orderDesc('createdAt'),  // newest first
    ]
});
```

You can chain multiple sort fields. The order of `orderAsc`/`orderDesc` calls determines priority:

```typescript
queries: [
    Query.orderDesc('priority'),   // sort by priority descending first
    Query.orderAsc('title'),       // then alphabetically by title
]
```

