## Limiting & Pagination

### Basic Limit & Offset

```typescript
const results = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.limit(25),    // max rows returned (default 25, max 100)
        Query.offset(0),    // skip N rows (not recommended for large datasets)
    ]
});
```

> **ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Offset performance:** `offset` becomes slow on large datasets because the database still scans skipped rows. Use **cursor-based pagination** for production.

### Cursor-Based Pagination (Recommended)

Use `cursorAfter` and `cursorBefore` with the `$id` of a known row:

```typescript
// First page ŌĆö get the first 20 rows
const page1 = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.limit(20),
        Query.orderAsc('$createdAt'),
    ]
});

// Next page ŌĆö use the last row's $id as cursor
const lastRowId = page1.documents[page1.documents.length - 1].$id;

const page2 = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.limit(20),
        Query.cursorAfter(lastRowId),   // rows after this ID
        Query.orderAsc('$createdAt'),
    ]
});

// Previous page
const page0 = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.limit(20),
        Query.cursorBefore(page1.documents[0].$id),  // rows before this ID
        Query.orderAsc('$createdAt'),
    ]
});
```

> **Important:** `cursorAfter`/`cursorBefore` require a consistent sort order. Always pair them with the same `orderAsc`/`orderDesc` you used to fetch the cursor row.

---

## Selecting Specific Fields

Reduce payload size by returning only the fields you need:

```typescript
const results = await tablesDB.listRows({
    databaseId: '[DATABASE_ID]',
    tableId: '[TABLE_ID]',
    queries: [
        Query.select(['title', 'content', 'status']),
        Query.equal('status', 'published'),
    ]
});
// Each document will only contain 'title', 'content', 'status', plus system fields ($id, $createdAt, etc.)
```

