Here's a complete example covering bucket creation (server-side), file upload (client-side), and image preview URL generation, all with permission configuration:

---

## Server-Side: Create a Bucket

Bucket creation requires an API key, so it's done server-side with `node-appwrite`:

```typescript
import { Client, Storage, ID, Permission, Role } from 'node-appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject(process.env.APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID!)
    .setKey(process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY!);

const storage = new Storage(client);

// Create a bucket with permissions
const bucket = await storage.createBucket({
    bucketId: ID.unique(),
    name: 'Images',
    permissions: [
        Permission.read(Role.any()),          // anyone can view files
        Permission.create(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),  // specific user can upload
        Permission.update(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),  // specific user can update
        Permission.delete(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),  // specific user can delete
    ],
    fileSecurity: true,    // enable per-file permissions (overrides bucket-level)
    maximumFileSize: 5242880,  // 5 MB max
    allowedFileExtensions: ['.jpg', '.jpeg', '.png', '.gif', '.webp'],
    compression: 'gzip',
    encryption: true,
    antivirus: true,
});

console.log('Bucket created:', bucket.$id);
```

> **`fileSecurity: true`** allows you to set per-file permissions on upload. If `false`, all files inherit the bucket's permissions.

---

## Client-Side: Upload a File & Get Preview URL

```typescript
import { Client, Storage, ID, Permission, Role } from 'appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('[PROJECT_ID]');

const storage = new Storage(client);

const BUCKET_ID = '[BUCKET_ID]';

// ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ Upload a file with per-file permissions ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
async function uploadImage(fileInput: HTMLInputElement) {
    const file = fileInput.files?.[0];
    if (!file) throw new Error('No file selected');

    const result = await storage.createFile({
        bucketId: BUCKET_ID,
        fileId: ID.unique(),
        file: file,
        permissions: [
            Permission.read(Role.any()),                        // public read
            Permission.update(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),         // only creator can update
            Permission.delete(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),         // only creator can delete
        ],
    });

    console.log('File uploaded:', result.$id);
    return result;
}

// ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ Get a preview URL for an image ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
function getImagePreview(fileId: string): string {
    // getFilePreview returns a URL string (no await needed)
    const previewUrl = storage.getFilePreview({
        bucketId: BUCKET_ID,
        fileId: fileId,
        width: 400,          // resize width in pixels
        height: 400,         // resize height in pixels
        gravity: 'center',   // crop gravity: 'top-left','top','top-right','left','center','right','bottom-left','bottom','bottom-right'
        quality: 80,         // image quality (1ŌĆō100)
        borderWidth: 2,      // border width in pixels
        borderColor: 'ff0000', // border hex color (no #)
        borderRadius: 10,    // border radius in pixels
        opacity: 100,        // opacity (0ŌĆō100)
        rotation: 0,         // rotation in degrees (0ŌĆō360)
        background: 'ffffff', // background hex for transparent images
        output: 'jpg',       // output format: 'jpg','png','webp'
    });

    return previewUrl; // e.g. "https://.../v1/storage/buckets/[BUCKET_ID]/files/[FILE_ID]/preview?..."
}

// ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ Full workflow ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
async function main() {
    const fileInput = document.getElementById('file-input') as HTMLInputElement;

    // 1. Upload
    const uploadedFile = await uploadImage(fileInput);

    // 2. Get preview URL
    const previewUrl = getImagePreview(uploadedFile.$id);

    // 3. Display the preview
    const img = document.createElement('img');
    img.src = previewUrl;
    img.alt = 'Image preview';
    document.body.appendChild(img);

    console.log('Preview URL:', previewUrl);
}
```

---

## HTML Companion

```html
<input type="file" id="file-input" accept="image/*" />
<button onclick="main()">Upload & Preview</button>
```

---

## Key Points

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Bucket creation** | Server-side only (requires API key via `node-appwrite`) |
| **`fileSecurity: true`** | Enables per-file permission overrides; otherwise bucket permissions apply to all files |
| **`Permission.read(Role.any())`** | Makes the file publicly readable ŌĆö required for preview URLs to work without auth |
| **`getFilePreview()`** | Returns a **URL string** synchronously (not a Promise); the URL can be used directly in `<img src>` |
| **Preview parameters** | All parameters (`width`, `height`, `quality`, etc.) are optional ŌĆö Appwrite generates the transformed image on-the-fly |
| **Common mistake** | Forgetting `Permission.read(...)` on the file or bucket makes it inaccessible, causing 401/403 errors on preview |

Here's a complete example that subscribes to both table row changes and file uploads simultaneously, using the `response.events` and `response.channels` arrays to differentiate and handle each event type:

```typescript
import { Client, Realtime, Channel } from 'appwrite';

// Initialize client
const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('[PROJECT_ID]');

const realtime = new Realtime(client);

// Define channel strings
const DATABASE_ID = '[DATABASE_ID]';
const TABLE_ID = '[TABLE_ID]';
const BUCKET_ID = '[BUCKET_ID]';

// Subscribe to both table row changes and file uploads at the same time
const subscription = await realtime.subscribe(
    [
        Channel.tablesdb(DATABASE_ID).table(TABLE_ID).row(),
        Channel.bucket(BUCKET_ID).file(),
    ],
    (response) => {
        const { events, payload, channels, timestamp } = response;

        // --- Handle table row events ---
        if (events.some((e) => e.includes('.rows.'))) {
            if (events.includes(`tablesdb.${DATABASE_ID}.tables.${TABLE_ID}.rows.*.create`)) {
                console.log('Ō£ģ New row created:', payload);
                // e.g., update UI list, show notification
            } else if (events.includes(`tablesdb.${DATABASE_ID}.tables.${TABLE_ID}.rows.*.update`)) {
                console.log('Ō£Å’ĖÅ Row updated:', payload);
                // e.g., refresh edited item in UI
            } else if (events.includes(`tablesdb.${DATABASE_ID}.tables.${TABLE_ID}.rows.*.delete`)) {
                console.log('­¤Śæ’ĖÅ Row deleted:', payload);
                // e.g., remove item from UI list
            }
            return; // done handling row event
        }

        // --- Handle file upload events ---
        if (events.some((e) => e.includes('.files.'))) {
            if (events.includes(`buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.create`)) {
                console.log('­¤ōü File uploaded:', payload);
                // e.g., refresh gallery, show upload success toast
            } else if (events.includes(`buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.update`)) {
                console.log('­¤ōØ File updated:', payload);
                // e.g., refresh file metadata display
            } else if (events.includes(`buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.delete`)) {
                console.log('­¤Śæ’ĖÅ File deleted:', payload);
                // e.g., remove file from gallery
            }
        }
    }
);

// Later, when you want to stop listening:
// await subscription.close();
```

## Key Points

1. **Multi-channel subscription** ŌĆö Pass an **array** of channel strings to `realtime.subscribe()` to listen to multiple resources in a single subscription. The callback fires for *any* event on *any* of the channels.

2. **Differentiating event types** ŌĆö Use `response.events` (an array of event strings) to determine what happened. Each event string follows the pattern:
   - Rows: `tablesdb.[DB_ID].tables.[TABLE_ID].rows.*.create|update|delete`
   - Files: `buckets.[BUCKET_ID].files.*.create|update|delete`

3. **The `payload`** ŌĆö Contains the affected resource (the row document or file metadata object), so you can immediately act on it.

4. **Unsubscribing** ŌĆö Call `await subscription.close()` to tear down the WebSocket listener when it's no longer needed (e.g., on component unmount in a SPA).

### Alternative: Separate subscriptions per concern

If you prefer cleaner separation of concerns, you can also create **two independent subscriptions** ŌĆö each with its own callback:

```typescript
const rowSub = await realtime.subscribe(
    Channel.tablesdb(DATABASE_ID).table(TABLE_ID).row(),
    (response) => {
        // Handle row events only
        console.log('Row event:', response.events, response.payload);
    }
);

const fileSub = await realtime.subscribe(
    Channel.bucket(BUCKET_ID).file(),
    (response) => {
        // Handle file events only
        console.log('File event:', response.events, response.payload);
    }
);

// Unsubscribe individually
// await rowSub.close();
// await fileSub.close();
```

Both approaches use a single underlying WebSocket connection ŌĆö Appwrite multiplexes all subscriptions over one socket, so there's no performance penalty for using separate subscriptions.

Here's the single `realtime.subscribe()` call that listens to both a table's rows and a bucket's files:

```typescript
import { Realtime, Channel } from 'appwrite';

const realtime = new Realtime(client);

const subscription = await realtime.subscribe(
    [
        Channel.tablesdb('[DATABASE_ID]').table('[TABLE_ID]').row(),
        Channel.bucket('[BUCKET_ID]').file(),
    ],
    (response) => {
        console.log(response.events);   // e.g. ['tablesdb.*.tables.*.rows.*.create']
        console.log(response.payload);  // the affected resource
    }
);
```

### Exact channel strings

The `Channel` builder produces these underlying strings:

| Builder | Channel String |
|---|---|
| `Channel.tablesdb('[DATABASE_ID]').table('[TABLE_ID]').row()` | `tablesdb.[DATABASE_ID].tables.[TABLE_ID].rows` |
| `Channel.bucket('[BUCKET_ID]').file()` | `buckets.[BUCKET_ID].files` |

So the equivalent call with raw strings would be:

```typescript
const subscription = await realtime.subscribe(
    [
        'tablesdb.[DATABASE_ID].tables.[TABLE_ID].rows',
        'buckets.[BUCKET_ID].files',
    ],
    (response) => { /* ... */ }
);
```

Replace `[DATABASE_ID]`, `[TABLE_ID]`, and `[BUCKET_ID]` with your actual IDs. To unsubscribe, call `await subscription.close()`.

